Responsibilities 


Assist in handling company secretarial matters relating to associated companies of the Group under various jurisdictions;
Maintain up-to-date records such as annual return and general meeting papers and attending to local filings;
Assist in preparing relevant minutes and various information for public disclosures, compliance issues and corporate exercises of the Group;
Perform ad hoc assignments as required.
Requirements


A degree holder with a student member of HKCGI;
Minimum 2 years’ experience in company secretarial field;
Experience in handling offshore companies is an advantage;
Proficiency in MS Office applications, Chinese Word Processing and CSA;
Excellent written and spoken English and Chinese. Mandarin is essential;
Good interpersonal and organization skills;
Meticulous, self-motivated, responsible and independent;
Immediately available is highly preferred.
Candidates with more experience will be considered as Senior Executive, Company Secretarial.


We provide competitive remuneration with career prospect to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your detailed resume with current & expected salary, contact number, availability with reference no.RA-CSE-2021 on subject line.

Corporate Office Address: 26/F, E-Trade Plaza, 24 Lee Chung Street, Chai Wan, Hong Kong (5 minutes' walking distance to MTR station)  

For more company information, please feel free to visit: www.rotam.com 

(Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.)

Job Responsibilities

Daily accounting entries, month-end closing and assist in handling full set of accounts of subsidiaries;
Perform general daily accounting functions such as A/P, A/R, journal, bank reconciliation, Intercompany reconciliation and etc.;
Assist in preparing monthly financial statement, costing and related month ended schedules;
Prepare Sales report;
Participate in ad hoc projects and tasks as assigned by Department Head.

Requirements

LCC & I Level 2 or above, Higher Certificate in Accounting is preferred;
3-5 years of accounting experience preferably in group companies;
Proficient in MS Office;
Experience in U8+ and Microsoft Dynamic 365 accounting system would be advantage;
Able to work under pressure;
Strong communication skills;
Immediate availabile is preferred.

Working Location: Hong Kong Science Park, Tai Po, N.T.

We offer 5-day working week and an attractive remuneration package. Interested party please submit your resume with current and expected salary by clicking “APPLY NOW”. For company details, please visit www.purapharm.com.

Our company is an equal opportunity employer. All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only, while the personal data of the unsuccessful applicants will be destroyed within 6 months after the recruitment process.

Trading Company in Kwai Chung invites candidates for the following post:

 Accounts Clerk

 Job Responsibilities:

Perform daily accounting duties, including prepare payment, receipt and journal vouchers, documents filing and full spectrum of book-keeping and accounting work;
Prepare monthly accounting schedules, bank reconciliations and reconcile intercompany balance and transactions;
Assist in month/year-end financial reporting, stocktaking and etc.; and
Ad hoc assignments as required.

Requirements:


Form 5 or above with LCC&I 3rd Level or above with min. 3 years relevant working experience;
Proficient in MS Office, advanced Excel skills would be an advantage and experience in using ERP;
Good command of spoken/written English and Chinese;
Mature, pro-active, strong sense of responsibility, analytical & detail-minded, able to work independently and good team player;
Immediate available is highly preferred.

Interested parties, please send your full resume stating career history, qualifications, current and expected salary, and availability to us by click “Apply Now” to submit your application.

Responsibilities


Develop company’s strategies / oversee implementation plans and monitor company’s finances;
Establish, review, execute policies and procedures to continuously improve efficiencies in Finance and compliance with other functions of company, i.e. IT, Legal etc. to meet requirements and business needs;
Maintain and monitor staffing, levels, knowledge-skills-attributes (KSA), expectations and motivation to fulfill organizational requirements;
Driving performance measures for operations considering efficiency versus effectiveness in in set comprehensive polices and goals to enrich company’s expansion in Macau or Australia’s various projects, campaigns, concerts, etc.;
Develop initiatives and policies that improve company growth in Macau and participate in expansion activities (investments, acquisitions, corporate alliances etc.);
Conduct analysis reports to senior management and board of directors;
Ensure smooth and effective collaboration with working partners and vendors in Macau / Australia;
Other ad hoc tasks as assigned.
Requirements


Bachelor degree or above preferably in Commerce, Accounting or related discipline;
Over 10+ years of senior management experience with laws & regulations in Macau / Australia;
At least 5 years working experience in entertainment, event & marketing industry;
Proficiency in Macau accounting standards, taxation, and other legal and compliance regulations;
Qualified accountant of HKICPA / ACCA / CPA Australia is a MUST;
Solid experience to prepare Conflict and Risk guidelines and procedures;
Good team player with sound interpersonal and communication skills to work with various business partners;
Strong analytical, managerial and leadership skills;
Proven problem-solving abilities and ability to work under tight deadlines;
Excellent command of English & Chinese.

Job Responsibilities:

Handle daily accounting transactions, operations, data input and filing;
Follow and monitor accounts payable transaction;
Prepare payment vouchers, cheques and accounting records;
Assist in Daily Worker Payroll;
Responsible for outdoor assignments such as cheques bank-in, etc.

Requirements:

Diploma or equivalent in above in Accounting; 
With LCCI level II and 3 years experience and experience in construction industry is an advantage;
Detail minded and good communication skills;
Able to work independently, Self-motivated and responsible;
Good command of MS office and accounting software;
Applicant with less experience will be considered as Senior Account Clerk.

Interested parties please apply with detailed resume stating expected salary and date of availability to Mr. Henry Fu via email by clicking "Apply Now" or fax to 2635 0611. 

[ Personal data collected will be used for recruitment-related purposes only. ]

Job Offers

Double Pay
Discretionary performance bonus
Marriage leave
Volunteer leave
Group Medical & Life Insurance coverage including dependents
Training sponsorship
Friendly working environment
Complimentary Shuttle bus service from Tsing Yi station to office (5 minutes’ drive way)

Key Responsibilities:

Manage overheads and support in all issues related to accounts payable and receivable;
Manage the suppliers’ invoices and payments;
Carry out cost studies, cost planning and control and cost analysis;
Ensure the agents account reconciliation are up to date and collection is done on time;
Review services contract with global legal team and the client;
Assist with Global Services Office operating cost control;
Other ad hoc duties as assigned.
Job Requirements:
Bachelor degree in Accounting/ Finance or above;
Minimum 6 years’ working experience in accounting field;
Excellent skill in MS Office application;
Proficient in verbal and written English and Chinese;
Mature and with pleasant personality;
Detail-oriented, able to handle multi-tasks and work under pressure.

Candidate with less experience will be considered as Accountant.

You are invited to send in your full CV by email to [via Apply Now ].

Information provided will be treated strictly confidential and only be used for recruitment purposes.

For more information of Aramex, please visit us at aramex.com.

Job Requirements:

Holder of DSE Certificate or above ;
1-2 years relevant experience ;
Good computer skills, MS Office;
Independent, hard-working and mature;



Responsibilities:

Handling full sets of book-keeping
Assist in accounts receivables, accounts payables and general ledger duties
Assist in month end closing and prepare accounting schedules and breakdown
Assist secretarial and administrative work
Assist in ad-hoc assignments



Interested candidates please send full resume with expected salary by clicking "Apply Now".


(Data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only)

Responsibilities:


Responsible for Accounts Payable daily operations including invoices and payments;
Ensure payments are supported and approved in compliance with internal policies;
Maintain proper and accurate records and supporting documents;
Liaise with internal and external parties regarding queries and disputes with their accounts;
Assist in financial closing in timely manner;
Assist to prepare AP reports and reconciliation;
Handle general filing and administration work;
Liaise with external auditors for the annual audit and other ad hoc tasks.

 Requirements - Qualification:


Higher diploma or above in Accounting or equivalent;
Minimum 2 to 3 years’ relevant working experience.

Requirements – Competences:


Good problem solving and presentation skills;
Able to work independently;
Diligent and proactive;
Numerical sensitive with analytical mindset and meticulous attention to detail. 

We look forward to receiving your application with detailed resume stating working experience, academic and language qualifications, existing and EXPECTED SALARY as well as availability. All applications will be kept strictly confidential.

We offer promising professional career and exposure to right candidate, together with attractive remuneration package including discretionary bonus, continuing education allowance, medical and dental coverage.

